title.narrative: Energy Districts in Colombia - Phase II

description.narrative: The project aims to foster sustainable urban development by further promoting and supporting the development of Energy Districts in Colombian cities, thus improving energy efficiency of cooling and heating utility services in buildings and cities infrastructure, in so doing reducing associated greenhouse gases emissions.. Building on the results of the first phase implemented directly by the Switzerland State Secretariat for Economic Affairs (SECO) together with Colombian partners, the project will work closely with national and subnational authorities and stakeholders to: 1. Improve and implement the national and subnational policy and regulatory frameworks to promote further development of Energy Dist ricts, 2. Reinforce knowledge and capacities for Energy Districts of all market players, as well as encourage collaboration among relevant stakeholders and further development of the value chain for Energy Districts. This will include the establishment of an Energy Districts competence center and the promotion of the exchange with know-how available in Swiss Academia and research institutions. The project will also technically assist 7-10 cities to include Energy Districts into their territorial/urban planning and support the realization of near-future mature projects.
